By Omololu Ogunmade in Abuja President Muhammadu Buhari this morning arrived Kaduna for a meeting with religious and traditional rulers over the recent crisis which claimed several lives in the state. The president who arrived the Kaduna Nigerian Airforce Base (NAF) at 10.10am in a presidential aircraft is currently at the Murtala Muhammed Square venue of the meeting. Among the traditional and religious present in the meeting are the Emir of Zazzau, Dr. Shehu Idris; Archbishop of Kaduna Catholic Archdiocese, Most Reverend Mathew Man-oso Ndagoso; and Secretary General of the Jama’atul Nasril Islam (JNI), Dr. Khalid Abubakar Aliyu.
Others are Chairman of the Christian Association of Nigeria (CAN), Bishop George Jonathan Dodo, and founder of the Peace Revival and Reconciliation Foundation of Nigeria, Pastor Yohanna Y.D. Buru. Details later…